In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Kayleigh McEnany discussed various topics, including the ongoing protests in Portland, the President's stance on law and order, the upcoming Republican convention, the President's phone call with Vladimir Putin, the renaming of military bases named after Confederate leaders, stimulus packages, drug pricing, and the closure of the Chinese consulate in Houston. McEnany also addressed questions about the President's changing tone on the coronavirus pandemic, the reopening of schools, federal law enforcement efforts, and funding for Operation LeGend.